<div class="module-container info-module">
    <p>We just added a stunning new book to the library: <em><a href="https://alliance-clark.primo.exlibrisgroup.com/permalink/01ALLIANCE_CC/3hpq3p/alma99900749460201861">We Will Go Right Up to the Sun: Female Pioneers of Geometric Abstraction</a></em>, published by Hirmer in 2024 to accompany an exhibition at the Wilhelm-Hack-Museum. The book reframes the history of geometric abstraction&mdash;a movement we often associate with a handful of famous men&mdash;by centering the women who shaped it, from Sophie Taeuber-Arp and Sonia Delaunay to lesser-known figures from Latin America and the Global South. It&#39;s lavishly illustrated, written in parallel German and English, and packed with essays covering everything from the Russian avant-garde to postwar Paris. If you&#39;re interested in art history, abstraction, or feminist perspectives on modernism, this one is well worth your time. Find it in the New Books section at Cannell Library.</p>
